ingredients:
6 garlic cloves, finely grated | 1 2" piece ginger, finely grated | 6 Tbsp. unsalted butter, cut into pieces | 5 Tbsp. low-sodium soy sauce | 3 Tbsp. mirin (sweet Japanese rice wine) | 2 tsp. toasted sesame oil | 1 lb. mixed tomatoes, halved, cut into wedges if large | 1 1-lb. bag frozen gyoza | Mixed tender herbs (such as cilantro leaves with tender stems
and/or basil leaves) and/or thinly sliced scallions and steamed white rice (for serving;
optional)
